==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petalism
<hw>Pet"al*ism</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧t"⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>petalismo`s</grk>, fr. <grk>pe`talon</grk> a leaf: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧talisme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A form
of sentence among the ancient Syracusans by which they banished for five
years a citizen suspected of having dangerous influence or ambition. It
was similar to the <sim>ostracism</sim> in Athens; but olive leaves were
used instead of shells for ballots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petalite</ent>⟦br⟧
